purpose: The commit fixes a bug related to queuing commands when HCI_UNREGISTER is set, preventing potential use-after-free (uaf) errors.
The commit removes an unnecessary include statement from a file, simplifying the code and reducing complexity.
The commit updates documentation for a store metric 'N/A' in perf-c2c, reflecting changes in the report table.
The commit addresses two key issues related to vma lock handling during split vma and range unmapping, ensuring proper synchronization and preventing potential issues.
The commit adds two new supplies, AVDD and MICVDD, to the rt5682s codec's binding in the device tree. It documents these supplies, which are already used by another device file.
The commit fixes a resource leak in the zorro7xx_remove_one() function by adding an iounmap() call to free the memory allocated by ioremap().
The commit removes an unused work field from a struct, which is a straightforward refactoring change.
The commit changes the type of key_idx from u8 to s8 in the cfg80211_auth_request struct, making it signed. This is done to avoid warnings from static checkers when the key is NULL.
The commit sorts CONFIG_SURFACE_PLATFORMS the same way savedefconfig does, making it a minor change to configuration files.

The commit introduces a new function mcp251xfd_is_fd_mode() to check if the chip's FIFOs are configured for CAN-FD mode, replacing an open-coded check. It also updates several files to use this new function.
The commit modifies selftests/rtc/rtctest.c to skip tests when RTC is not present, adding checks for file existence and skipping tests if the file does not exist.
The commit removes a redundant assignment to variable bytes, which was causing a clang scan build warning about dead code.

The commit decouples the presence of rcuscale from the presence of RCU Tasks, allowing CONFIG_PREEMPT_NONE=y kernels to build rcuscale without RCU Tasks. This change is made by modifying Kconfig.debug and rcuscale.c files.
The commit appears to be a refactoring change, removing duplicated text in a header file. The purpose is to improve code readability.

The commit reverts a change that populates the dcn315 clk table based on dcfclk, due to potential underflow issues when dcfclk states are disabled. The revert is intended to prevent this issue until a better solution is implemented.
The commit adds a compatible string for the Renesas RZ/V2L SoC's Bifrost Mali-G31 GPU to the device tree bindings.
The commit renames struct pcie_port to dw_pcie_rp for consistency with other names in the DW PCIe core driver entities.
The commit fixes a clang -Wformat warning by changing the format specifier in netdev_dbg from %#06hx to %#06x, which is more accurate given that the argument will be promoted to an int.
The commit fixes a bug related to branch range check in MIPS architecture, preventing potential negative offset issues.
The commit removes an unnecessary case from SetHwReg8188EU() by directly calling a function, simplifying the code.
The commit declares non-global symbols as static to fix sparse warnings introduced while adding errata, indicating a good comprehension of the main changes and their purpose.
The commit is a bug-fixing commit that removes bogus interrupt flags from MDSS nodes in the device tree bindings, ensuring correct configuration for the display subsystem.
The commit modifies the v4l2-ctrls API to allocate arrays in ctrl_ref, allowing for dynamic array size changes from drivers.
The commit adds support for new SoCs and PMICs to the socinfo driver, improving its functionality.

The commit is related to the RTL8XXXU driver, specifically recognizing all possible chip cuts (A-P) instead of printing 'unknown' when it's greater than E. The changes are made in the rtl8xxxu_core.c file.
The commit removes a custom software enable count from PRCMU clocks, as the core already keeps a software enable count.
The commit aims to remove #ifdef CONFIG_XIP_KERNEL usage by grouping related code together, improving code organization and reducing unnecessary conditional compilation.
The commit enables QUP and GPI DMA hardware to add functioning I2C nodes later, which implies a change in the device tree configuration.
The commit is a bug-fixing commit that corrects comments, fixes typos, and improves coding style.

The commit fixes an infinite loop issue in the release_swfw_sync function, which occurs when failing to acquire the HW semaphore due to surprise removal of hardware. The fix involves checking if the semaphore is acquired and logging an error if it's not.
The commit updates the pcm3168a driver to use modern ASoC DAI format terminology, replacing old style defines for bus clocks.
The commit removes a hack for future NFS swap support, which is no longer needed as IS_SWAPFILE is always defined.
The commit implements GTP echo response, adding functionality to handle echo requests without a userspace daemon.
The commit replaces cpumask_next_* functions with cpumask_first_* where appropriate, improving code quality by providing more effective analogues for certain operations.

The commit removes a call to 'dtim_assoc' IOVAR, which is no longer supported in the firmware, causing a failure when trying to get TIM information from firmware. This change ensures that the host driver will no longer try to get TIM information from firmware.
The commit adds support for a new platform without amplifier, specifically adding a board config adl_rt5682 to support alc5682 headset codec.
The commit modifies the io_uring/net.c file to fail zc sendmsg when unsupported by socket, indicating a change in behavior related to zerocopy operations.

The commit modifies the kerneldoc-preamble.sty file to conditionally load xeCJK depending on the existence of the Noto Sans CJK font, improving the situation where texlive-xecjk can be installed/removed independently of other texlive packages.
The commit modifies the checkpatch.pl script to allow 'case' macros, which are used in some in-kernel drivers.
The commit replaces simple-KMS helpers with atomic helpers, improving code sharing among drivers.
The commit adds a jpeg decode worker interface to ensure three HWs run in parallel in MT8195, improving performance.
The commit removes pointless VPRINTK() calls and ata_scsi_dump_cdb(), improving code quality and reducing noise in dmesg output.
The commit adds support for zstate during extended vblank, improving performance by utilizing extra vblank period to enter z9/z10 states.
The commit fixes a bug by updating the function pointer prototype to match reality, preventing CFI violations when booting a kernel compiled with CONFIG_CFI_CLANG on certain machines.
The commit corrects a property name in a YAML file, adding missing 'additionalProperties' to prevent future errors.
The commit silences an array-bounds warning on GCC 12 by adding a flag to suppress this specific warning in non-W=1+ builds.

The commit changes the pm_runtime_get_sync call to pm_runtime_resume_and_get in sun8i-ss-prng.c, which is a simplification of code. The purpose is to use a more appropriate function for this scenario.
The commit splits out fixed file installation and removal from the io_uring code, moving it to the filetable code where it belongs. It also changes the helpers to take a ctx rather than an io_kiocb.
The commit updates the dt-bindings for the nxp, imx8mq-vpu to support separate nodes for G1 and G2 decoders. It also removes deprecated properties.
The commit removes an unused macro definition, simplifying the code by combining its contents into another macro.
